"Whatever mix of cloud services an organisation opts into, security can't be considered as an afterthought. The data businesses possess can be their most valuable asset, so cloud security should be a top priority. There are three ‘pillars’ businesses need to consider – risk assessment, a cloud supplier capable of offering transparent communication regarding security, and one with a proactive stance to sharing its security implementations and controls, argues Chris Jenkins of Dimension Data. Speaking in very general terms, cloud computing and the concept of ‘the cloud’ were probably the most over-hyped terms in the history of the IT industry. Cloud may never get away from this perception. Yet, regardless of the early hype, you'd be hard-pressed to find anyone who didn't admit the industry has embraced the benefits of cloud computing. Even the heavyweights like Gartner have stated businesses and the technology industry have moved past the hyped phase of cloud adoption, and are now actually using cloud services to drive business benefits, efficiencies and innovation. 1"
